    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Ensure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 mins)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-lean-beef-and-mushroom-spaghetti/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>mince</strong> with a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-lean-beef-and-mushroom-spaghetti/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mince is cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-lean-beef-and-mushroom-spaghetti/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>pasta</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat </p><p>Cook the pasta for 7-9 min (10\u201312 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite </p><p>Once done, drain the pasta, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-lean-beef-and-mushroom-spaghetti/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mince has browned, tear your <strong>chestnut mushrooms </strong>into the pan</p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with most of your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika </strong>(save a little for garnish!)<strong> </strong>and cook for a further 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-lean-beef-and-mushroom-spaghetti/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>and <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [180ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>mustard stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-lean-beef-and-mushroom-spaghetti/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>mustard stock</strong> and<strong> </strong>your<strong> soft cheese</strong> to the pan with the <strong>drained pasta</strong>, 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[85ml]</span> <strong>reserved starchy pasta water </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for a further 2 min until the pasta is well coated in sauce and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>smoky mince & mushroom pasta</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-lean-beef-and-mushroom-spaghetti/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>smoky lean beef & mushroom pasta </strong>in a bowl</p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>remaining ground smoked paprika</strong> and season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
